# 51_export_theme_smoke — third format-verb on the export Scriptable
# from ARC m5b (s253 m1). Lands on the now-open `export` singleton
# (opened at s251 m1 with svg); adds the freedesktop icon-theme
# bundle verb. **No Tier 4 row tick** — verb-on-existing-singleton.
# Export verb surface widens 2/5 → 3/5.
#
# `theme <dir>` is the THIRD format-verb on this Scriptable. First
# directory-output verb on any m5b headless-verb singleton (the
# helper writes a TREE of files under <dir>, not a single file).
# Naming: `theme` rather than `ico` because the bundle is a
# freedesktop icon theme (consumable by GTK apps and system-wide
# hicolor installations), not a Windows `.ico` file. The
# architecture-text references to `export ico` in CANON / ARC /
# HANDOFF were swept to `export theme` at the s253 m1 doc sweep
# alongside this code-side ship.
#
# ── What this smoke exercises ─────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# `export theme <dir>` has a five-case contract (see ExportScriptable.hpp
# for the full design block):
#
#   Branch A (happy path):     project loaded + project has a path +
#                              safe directory + write succeeds. Writes
#                              the freedesktop icon-theme bundle tree
#                              under <dir>, captures path + ok into
#                              per-attempt observables, returns ok.
#   Branch B (wrong args):     zero / multiple / non-string args.
#                              Refuses with "expected exactly one
#                              path argument". Same-shape as svg.
#   Branch C (empty path):     empty string or non-string arg. Refuses
#                              with "path argument is empty or not a
#                              string". Same-shape as svg.
#   Branch D (unsafe path):    path_is_safe refused. Refuses with the
#                              utility's reason string (outside $HOME
#                              and $TMPDIR / realpath failed / etc).
#                              SIXTH production call site of
#                              path_is_safe (after save_as s247 m1,
#                              load s249 m1, new s250 m1, svg s251
#                              m1, png s252 m2); THIRD call site on
#                              the export Scriptable.
#   Branch E (NoProject):      m_project null. Refuses.
#   Branch F (NoProjectPath):  m_project loaded but its directory is
#                              empty — the project hasn't been saved.
#                              NEW BRANCH not present on svg / png:
#                              theme derives theme_name from the
#                              project's directory basename, so a
#                              never-saved project has no usable
#                              theme_name. Refusal points the script
#                              author at proj save_as.
#   Branch G (IoFailed):       export_theme returned success=false.
#                              Helper's error_message is interpolated
#                              into the throw. Several sub-causes:
#                              cannot create output_dir; no valid
#                              icons after filtering (project has
#                              zero documents OR every document has
#                              empty export_name / export_category);
#                              every per-doc write failed. The
#                              "project has zero documents" case
#                              surfaces HERE rather than as a
#                              NoActiveDoc branch (theme exports
#                              EVERY document, not the active one;
#                              the absence of an active doc has no
#                              meaning for this verb).
#
# This smoke exercises Branch A twice (different paths) plus Branches C
# and D as the assertable edge cases. Branches B / E / F / G are
# documented at the bottom with the manual setup steps to reach them.
# Branch F (NoProjectPath) in particular is interesting because it's
# the new branch unique to theme — exercising it requires running
# the smoke against a never-saved project, which contradicts the
# smoke's general assumption of running on a saved project.
#
# Coverage shape (matches smoke 49 / smoke 50's BUILD UP / VALIDATE /
# FIND EDGES discipline):
#
#   - BUILD UP        : Phase 1 inspects initial query state.
#                       NOTE: this smoke is typically run after smokes
#                       49 (svg) and 50 (png) in the same session, so
#                       last_path will reflect the prior smoke's last
#                       successful export. Phase 1's asserts are
#                       written for the fresh-session case; see the
#                       NOTE below the asserts for the run-after-50
#                       caveat.
#   - VALIDATE        : Phase 2 issues the happy-path export to a
#                       /tmp directory. Phase 3 asserts both
#                       observables flipped correctly (last_ok ==
#                       true, last_path == supplied dir).
#   - FIND EDGES      : Phases 4-6 exercise refusal paths (empty
#                       path, unsafe path), confirming each
#                       preserves last_path while flipping last_ok
#                       back to false.
#   - VALIDATE again  : Phase 7 issues a second happy-path export to
#                       a different /tmp directory. Phase 8 confirms
#                       last_path updated to the new path.
#
# The two refused calls produce listener-error lines but no project
# state mutation — same property smokes 45-50 confirmed for the
# respective refusals.
#
# ── Caller context ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This smoke runs through ScripterWindow's listener, m_context =
# RunContext::Scripter. `export theme` declares its mask as
# Scripter | TestRunner — THE SAME MASK AS svg and png. Same trust
# rationale: theme produces SIDE ARTEFACTS (a tree of files under
# <dir>), it does not rewrite the project's identity. The path-
# containment gate covers the system-integrity layer; Macro
# exclusion covers the recorded-automation layer.
#
# NINTH consumer of Scriptable::context_mask() in the codebase
# (Inspector + proj.{save, save_as, close, load, new} +
# export.{svg, png, theme}). Registry-promotion clock at 9/n;
# STILL HELD by design — catalogue is getting MORE uniform
# (seven of nine verbs share Scripter | TestRunner), which
# weakens rather than strengthens the dedup argument. One verb
# away from the ~10 catalogue-size promotion trigger.
#
# ── Test isolation ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# `export theme` WRITES TO DISK — produces a TREE of side artefacts
# under the two directories named below, both under /tmp. The smoke
# does NOT modify project content (no objects added / removed /
# edited, no save / save_as / close / load fired). Effect: two
# directory trees materialise in /tmp, each containing:
#
#   <dir>/
#     scalable/<category>/<name>-symbolic.svg          (one per included doc)
#     16x16/<category>/<name>-symbolic.png             (and 24x24, 32x32, 48x48,
#                                                       64x64, 128x128, 256x256)
#     gresource.xml
#     index.theme
#     README.md
#
# Manual teardown (the DSL has no `fs.remove` verb today):
#
#   rm -rf /tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme /tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme_v2
#
# Safe to run repeatedly — each run overwrites the prior run's
# outputs (ensure_dir is idempotent; write_text and the PNG writer
# both truncate on open).
#
# ── Precondition reminders ───────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# This smoke assumes:
#   1. A project is loaded (any project; the smoke does not depend
#      on specific content).
#   2. The project has been SAVED at least once — m_project->directory
#      is non-empty. Without this, every `export theme` call in the
#      smoke refuses with NoProjectPath at Branch F and the asserts
#      in Phases 3 and 8 fail (last_ok stays false).
#   3. The project has at least one document with non-empty
#      export_name and export_category (set via the inspector's
#      Icon Export section). Without this, the helper's "No icons
#      to export" branch fires and the asserts in Phases 3 and 8
#      fail (last_ok stays false; the throw carries the helper's
#      error_message).
#
# Preconditions 2 and 3 are stricter than smoke 49's. Smoke 49 only
# needed a project + an active doc; it didn't care whether the doc
# had export_name set. Theme cares because the writer skips docs
# without an export_name AND fails the whole export if the result
# of skipping is zero valid entries. The minimum viable project
# for this smoke: one saved project + one doc with export_name and
# export_category set.

#[sub] === Phase 1: initial-state precondition ===

#[sub] Get the most-recent-successful-export path. At session start
#[sub] (or before the first successful export this session), it's the
#[sub] empty string. Operator-visual on the empty echo.
#[sub]
#[sub] NOTE: if you've already run smokes 49 or 50 in the current
#[sub] session, last_path will reflect the prior smoke's last
#[sub] successful export (probably /tmp/curvz_smoke_50_export_v2.png
#[sub] from smoke 50's Phase 7). The two asserts below will fail in
#[sub] that case; the smoke is designed to land cleanly on a fresh
#[sub] session. Same posture as smokes 49 and 50.

get export last_path

assert export last_ok == false
assert export last_path == ""

#[sub] === Phase 2: happy-path export (Branch A) ===

#[sub] Issue the verb. Expected trace line:
#[sub]
#[sub]   > export theme "/tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme"
#[sub]   ok
#[sub]
#[sub] Operator-visual on the `ok` echo. Side effects:
#[sub]   - Curvz::export_theme writes the icon-theme bundle tree
#[sub]     under /tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme.
#[sub]   - LOG_INFO line: "export theme: wrote N icons to '/tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme'".
#[sub]   - m_last_path updated to the supplied directory.
#[sub]   - m_last_ok flipped to true.
#[sub]
#[sub] No project-state mutation — m_project, m_history, the dirty
#[sub] indicator on the title bar are all unchanged. Export produces
#[sub] a tree of side artefacts; the project remains identifiable
#[sub] by its own .curvz directory.

export theme "/tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme"

#[sub] === Phase 3: post-success assertable observables ===

#[sub] Both queries reflect the just-completed successful export.
#[sub] These two asserts are THE STRUCTURAL PROOF that the verb body
#[sub] ran to completion — the DSL's assert can't directly compare
#[sub] against the listener's `ok` echo line (assert is equality-only
#[sub] on query results), so the queries are the assertable
#[sub] observable standing in for the ok echo.

assert export last_ok == true
assert export last_path == "/tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme"

#[sub] === Phase 4: empty-path refusal (Branch C) ===

#[sub] Call theme with an empty path argument. The Scriptable's
#[sub] argument-validation guard fires before path_is_safe and
#[sub] before the helper:
#[sub]
#[sub]   > export theme ""
#[sub]   error invoke threw: export theme: path argument is empty or not a string
#[sub]
#[sub] Operator-visual on the refusal text. The refusal:
#[sub]   - Flips m_last_ok to false (no successful export just happened).
#[sub]   - Does NOT clear m_last_path — it still points at the prior
#[sub]     success's path. Same design choice as svg / png.

export theme ""

#[sub] === Phase 5: refusal preserves last_path, flips last_ok ===

#[sub] The two structural properties the smoke is here to confirm
#[sub] about refusal semantics. last_ok flipped to false (no current
#[sub] success); last_path UNCHANGED from Phase 2's value (the prior
#[sub] success's observable survives a refusal).

assert export last_ok == false
assert export last_path == "/tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme"

#[sub] === Phase 6: unsafe-path refusal (Branch D) ===

#[sub] Call theme with a directory outside $HOME and $TMPDIR.
#[sub] path_is_safe refuses with the structured reason string:
#[sub]
#[sub]   > export theme "/etc/curvz_smoke_51_etc"
#[sub]   error invoke threw: export theme: outside $HOME and $TMPDIR
#[sub]
#[sub] Operator-visual on the refusal text. The reason string comes
#[sub] from path_is_safe's reason_out parameter — same string svg's
#[sub] Phase 6 and the proj save_as / load / new smokes would see.
#[sub]
#[sub] SIXTH production call site of curvz::scripting::path_is_safe
#[sub] (after save_as s247 m1, load s249 m1, new s250 m1, svg s251
#[sub] m1, png s252 m2); THIRD call site on the export Scriptable.
#[sub] The utility's file-vs-directory neutrality is now exercised
#[sub] across two distinct path shapes (file path on svg/png/save_as/
#[sub] load/new; directory path on theme); the same gate that
#[sub] protected /etc/foo.svg also protects /etc/my-theme/.
#[sub]
#[sub] No assertions follow this refusal — Phase 5's structural
#[sub] properties (last_ok flips false, last_path preserved) already
#[sub] established the contract.

export theme "/etc/curvz_smoke_51_etc"

#[sub] === Phase 7: second happy-path export (different directory) ===

#[sub] Re-export to a DIFFERENT /tmp directory. Two distinct
#[sub] successful exports back-to-back exercise the "last_path
#[sub] updates on every success" semantic — Phase 8's assertion is
#[sub] that last_path now points at the NEW directory, not the
#[sub] Phase-2 directory.

export theme "/tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme_v2"

#[sub] === Phase 8: last_path updated to the new path ===

#[sub] last_ok back to true (we just succeeded). last_path now equal
#[sub] to the Phase-7 directory, not the Phase-2 directory.
#[sub] Structural proof that consecutive successful exports correctly
#[sub] update the observable to the most recent target — across two
#[sub] different formats now, this also confirms the cross-format
#[sub] last_path sharing semantic (Phases 2 and 7 are both `theme`
#[sub] calls, but the same update discipline applies if Phase 7
#[sub] were a different format).

assert export last_ok == true
assert export last_path == "/tmp/curvz_smoke_51_theme_v2"

#[sub] s253 m1 smoke complete. Expected summary line:
#[sub]
#[sub]   13 lines, 8 pass, 0 fail, 2 error
#[sub]
#[sub] - 8 PASS  : 2 (Phase 1 initial state) + 2 (Phase 3 post-success)
#[sub]             + 2 (Phase 5 refusal-preserves) + 2 (Phase 8 second-
#[sub]             success-updates)
#[sub] - 2 error : the two verb-body refusals at Phases 4 and 6
#[sub]             (empty-path and unsafe-path; intentional — the
#[sub]             argument-validation guard and path_is_safe gate
#[sub]             working as designed)
#[sub] - 1 operator-visual : the `get export last_path` echo at Phase 1
#[sub] - 2 operator-visual `ok` echoes : the two successful exports
#[sub]             at Phases 2 and 7
#[sub] - 2 operator-visual refusals : the structured `error invoke
#[sub]             threw:` lines under each refused export
#[sub]
#[sub] EXACT MATCH to smoke 49's predicted counts (13 lines, 8 pass,
#[sub] 0 fail, 2 error) — the contract is identical minus the size
#[sub] dimension which neither verb has. This is the cleanest
#[sub] prediction-streak entry to forecast since the discipline-
#[sub] transfer property held across both s251 m1 and s252 m2 fix
#[sub] / first-ship landings: if the structural shape that landed
#[sub] on svg transferred cleanly to png at s252 m2, the same shape
#[sub] should transfer cleanly to theme here. The smoke is the
#[sub] structural check; observed counts matching predicted is the
#[sub] discipline-transfer confirmation.
#[sub]
#[sub] Tier 4 row stays at 2/~4-5 (verb-on-existing-singleton, no
#[sub] tick). Export surface widens 2/5 → 3/5. path_is_safe gains
#[sub] its sixth production call site and third cross-Scriptable
#[sub] application. context_mask() consumer count goes 8 → 9
#[sub] (registry-promotion clock held at 9/n by design — catalogue
#[sub] is becoming MORE uniform across consumers, not less).
#[sub]
#[sub] m5b export-surface arc continues to widen: refpt and
#[sub] gresource remain. After those land, the `app` singleton's
#[sub] `quit` is the natural next opener; the third Tier 4 tick
#[sub] (2 → 3) happens then.

#[sub] ── Manual exercise for the other branches ─────────────────────
#[sub]
#[sub] Branch B (wrong-args): call `export theme` with zero or two
#[sub] args:
#[sub]
#[sub]   > export theme
#[sub]   error invoke threw: export theme: expected exactly one path argument
#[sub]
#[sub]   > export theme "/tmp/a" "/tmp/b"
#[sub]   error invoke threw: export theme: expected exactly one path argument
#[sub]
#[sub] Branch E (NoProject — no project loaded): rare; can occur
#[sub] transiently during a project close sequence. Manually
#[sub] reachable by File ▸ Close Project, then running theme in
#[sub] Scripter before opening a new project:
#[sub]
#[sub]   > export theme "/tmp/foo"
#[sub]   error invoke threw: export theme: no project loaded
#[sub]
#[sub] Branch F (NoProjectPath — new branch unique to theme): start
#[sub] Curvz, do NOT load or save a project, then call theme:
#[sub]
#[sub]   > export theme "/tmp/foo"
#[sub]   error invoke threw: export theme: project has no path (save the project with proj save_as first)
#[sub]
#[sub] Branch G (IoFailed): the most reachable variant is "no valid
#[sub] icons" — load a project where no documents have export_name
#[sub] and export_category set, then call theme:
#[sub]
#[sub]   > export theme "/tmp/foo"
#[sub]   error invoke threw: export theme: No icons to export. Assign a name and category to each icon in the inspector.
#[sub]
#[sub] Alternative IoFailed variant: chmod -w a target directory's
#[sub] parent before running the smoke; ensure_dir's mkdir call
#[sub] will fail and the helper returns IoFailed with a "Cannot
#[sub] create output directory" message.
#[sub]
#[sub] All refusal branches share the listener's standard error-throw
#[sub] convention: `error invoke threw: <message>` with the message
#[sub] text matching the strings in ExportScriptable.cpp.
